<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="short-adj">short <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ʃɔːt/    美 /ʃɔːrt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-long-tall">1.★ <strong>(长度、时间) 短的 反 long；近的；矮的 反 tall：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>cut / make a long story short
长话短说</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The bus stop is a short way off.
公交车站离这儿不远。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He is too short to become a basketball player.
他个子太矮，当不了篮球运动员。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>不足的；缺乏的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Guide dogs are short in number.
导盲犬数量不足。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>These goods <strong>are short in supply</strong>.
这些货物供应短缺。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>简短的；简洁的；缩写的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>His answer was short and to the point.
他的回答简明切题。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="be-short-for">(be) short for</h3>
<p>1.<strong>为…的缩写 / 简称：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>UN is short for United Nations.
UN是UnitedNations的简称。</p></div>

<h3 id="be-short-of">(be) short of</h3>
<p>1.<strong>缺乏；不足：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He is short of funds right now.
眼下他资金短缺。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The report seemed to be short of facts.
这个报告似乎缺乏事实依据。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>That young man is honest, cooperative, always there when you need his help. <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (简言之), he’s reliable.  （2016 浙江改）  </li>
<li>— Why didn’t you buy the camera you had longed for?
— I had planned to, but I was £50 <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (缺少的).  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. In short / In a word  2. short  </p></div>